column4: dami dōbu = damidō (a lot of animal)
dami shan lando = damshanlan (a lot of mountain land)
ēsu + pa = ēspa island (west part island)
yenabaku (old name for desert) + lupa = inabalupa (desert area)
layo nōsu lupa = lînospa (far north area)
tumang + rabi = tumbi valley (fox and rabbit valley)
fung + mūn + lando = fūmunlan (full moon land)
Bāk City (from Bark which is an onomatopoeia)
